4 SYNOPSIS:
5 Under existing law, as part of the Underground
6 Damage Prevention Program, an operator of an
7 underground utility facility must respond to a request
8 to locate the facility for design or surveying purposes
9 within a minimum time frame using specific methods.
10 This bill would remove providing locate
11 requestors with a description of the underground
12 facilities and allowing these requestors to view
13 facility records from those methods by which operators
14 may respond to locate requests.
15 This bill would require operators to complete
16 locate requests that have not been completed within 20
17 calendar days of being submitted to the One-Call
18 Notification System before completing any other locate
19 request or other marking of facilties.
20 This bill would make operators liable for any
21 costs incurred by a requestor due to project delay
22 because a locate request remains incomplete 30 calendar
23 days or more after being submitted to the system.
24 This bill would prohibit a contract locator from
25 closing a locate request for purposes of the system.
26 This bill would also prohibit an operator from
27 closing a locate request for purposes of the system
28 unless the operator has field-verified that the
